(59, 59, 'product_cat', '<h2>Shag Rugs And Kilim Ottomans.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"block-heading-text\">Their long, shaggy fibers and deep pile is what gives a shag carpet that long, plushy feel under your feet. A cultural relic iconic of the 1960s and 70s, shag rugs have resurged in popularity in recent years and transformed to encompass and blend today’s styles, as well as retain the retro feel of the Swinging’ Sixties and Disco Era.</div>', 0, 0),
(60, 60, 'product_cat', '<h2>Animal Prints / Cowhides Rugs</h2>\r\n<div class=\"block-heading-text\">Sustainably sourced from both India and the South American pampas, each one-of-a-kind cowhide rug has a lustrous sheen, contrasting spots, and a broad range of background hues that come alive in natural daylight.</div>', 0, 1),
(61, 61, 'product_cat', 'Tapestries are woven on a vertical loom, often feature complex, pictorial designs equivalent in comparison to paintings, and visible from both front and back.', 0, 0),
